Text: The summary of the fourth week is concise : )Coding, coding and coding, and discussion, and discussion and discussion.
My three teammates did a great job this week.
I am aware that I am far, far away behind them.
I know how the software should work, but Bibi, Gogo and Roro do the real job, especially right now when all the parts have to be bound, hooked, merged etc.
I will not be ever a real programmer.
Frankly speaking, I have never wanted to be, and all these projects only confirm what I've been thinking.
I am delighted that I know what is going on behind the scene, but it is not my passion.
I am impressed with the guys' knowledge and the will to solve the problems.
What is the more crucial they still have the patience to meðŸ˜Š and explain to me how they bind the individual parts.
I only say to them:  I would like to this button save this particular thing.
I can create buttons and the design (not using only drag and drop, but writing the code) and bind to the other window.
Still, the connection with the database is something I can not handle in this project, especially using MVVM:  too many windows, too many models, too many view models, services etc.
It is excellent that my colleagues know what they are doing.
I am not sure if using the View Model solution is the best one.
It is not the easiest one for sure.
We have tried to prepare the research, but maybe it was still not enough?
Right now, we have to deal with this solution.
We hade a meeting in a hospital with the client as usually on Monday.
We try to dispel our doubts and ask if we think correct.
They always have something to add, but they are very excited about a possible solution.
Besides the meeting with the client, we met three times last week to work together for a few hours and solve the problems together.
I think that it helps all of us.
